7: tmux enables a number of terminals (or windows) to be accessed and
8: controlled from a single terminal like screen. tmux runs as a
9: server-client system. A server is created automatically when necessary
10: and holds a number of sessions, each of which may have a number of
11: windows linked to it. Any number of clients may connect to a session,
12: or the server may be controlled by issuing commands with tmux.
13: Communication takes place through a socket, by default placed in /tmp.
14: Moreover tmux provides a consistent and well-documented command
15: interface, with the same syntax whether used interactively, as a key
16: binding, or from the shell. It offers a choice of vim or Emacs key
